# Data Privacy (Mexico)

- Comply with **LFPDPPP**: lawful basis, privacy notice (aviso de privacidad), consent for marketing.
- Collect minimum data: name, email, shipping, optional RFC for invoicing (CFDI) - document purpose in UI.

```tsx
// GOOD: consent checkbox for promos, not for order fulfillment
<Checkbox {...register('marketingConsent')} />
<label>{t('privacy.marketingConsent')}</label>
<p>{t('privacy.noticeLink')}</p>
```

- Honor ARCO requests: access, rectification, cancellation, opposition - CRM admin workflow within 20 days SLA target.
- Retention: delete/anonymize inactive accounts per policy; keep invoices per SAT requirements separately.
- Cross-border: if US-hosted (Netlify, Stripe), disclose in aviso; use DPAs with processors.
- No selling customer lists; analytics must be anonymized or consented.
